<html t:type="layout" title="Home"
      xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_1_0.xsd"
      xmlns:p="tapestry:parameter">
        
		<h2 class="fontface">What is <span class="titleBold">opos</span>?</h2>
		
		<p>
			<b>OPOS</b> is a free service which enables easy interchanging of user's Online Presence data (such as 
			posts, statuses, current activities and many more) between	different applications. Users can specify 
			which Instant Messaging and Social Network applications they are using (among supported ones by OPOS) 
			and OPOS will automatically enable communication between those applications and exchanging of relevant 
			data between them.<br/>
			OPOS is still in beta phase and there is more applications and functionalities to 
			come.</p>
			
		<h2 class="fontface">How it works?</h2>
		<p>
			<img class="floatLeft" src="${asset:context:images/bullet-01.png}" alt="" width="47" height="47" />
			<br/>
			Easily register an account on OPOS. 
			<br/>
		</p>
			
		<p>
			<img class="floatLeft" src="${asset:context:images/bullet-02.png}" alt="" width="47" height="47" />
			Chose which applications you are using and want to be included in Online Presence data interchanging.
		</p>
		
		<p>
			<img class="floatLeft" src="${asset:context:images/bullet-03.png}" alt="" width="47" height="47" />
			Sit back and watch how OPOS efficiently updates your posts, chat statuses, current activities... from 
			one application to another. 
		</p>
			
		<t:pagelink t:page="SignUp" class="btnCreateAccount">Create account</t:pagelink>
		
		<span class="orSign">or <t:pagelink t:page="Login">Sign in</t:pagelink></span>
				
		<div class="hr"></div>
</html>
